cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.EC, cs.CSCW 

This paper discusses the issue of minimum wage in crowd work, which involves the intersection of computer science and social issues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and social computing (SI), as it surveys Requesters and workers and examines their opinions on the issue. Additionally, the paper discusses economic and pragmatic factors, which could fall under the category of cs.EC (Economics and Computation). Finally, the paper involves collaboration and communication among workers and Requesters, which could fall under the category of cs.CSCW (Computer-Supported Cooperative Work).
